result.name: Super Super Congee & Noodles

reviews.text: Economic prices. Breakfast lots of choices combination. Western bacon egg to Chinese congee fried noodles or glutinous rice dumplings. Fast food seating but comfortable.

Tried the fish belly congee here. Although the rice of the congee had a good texture, it tasted WAY too fishy. It is hard to eat because there are a lot of small bones to take out as I was eating it. Also, the congee was a bit pricy and I had a tummy ache after eating this dish. I ended up not finishing this dish. 

If you come here, I recommend other dishes, like their fish congee with parsley. 

3/10
A popular restaurants with standard food sets that don't often make sense. Meats and fish are undercooked, but locals seem to like it.  Staff are very nice to my family and I.

I love Cantonese congee and this is pretty much the only place that serves it in the vicinity. Used to love their liver congee but that's no longer on the menu. It isn't the greatest, will do. Rest of the food is acceptable.
The service here is very unstable. Once I found a fly in my dish and the staff unhappily used the same bowl to serve me without any apology.
